examples.en: He wept at the news of her death.
The poor woman wept her thanks.
He wept bitter tears of disappointment.
She wept for her broken dreams and lost youth.
She wept for the loss of her mother.
Marion sank down on a rock, and wept.
I flung myself into his arms and wept.
She wept harder and honked into her hanky.
The mother of the murder victim wept in court.
An angel watching an urn wept over her, carved in stone.
Peter broke down and wept when he saw the deer that he had shot.
He wept bitterly (=cried a lot) when it was time for us to leave.
